subSubSection.paragraph:
Finally, the structure of the respiratory system of 

Podotarsonemus

is mostly uniform throughout the genus, with one notable exception (the species from 
India
). In most species the system is paired, with each stigma leading to a single trachea that runs into a very lightly sclerotized atrium. Distally, each trachea emerges from the atrium and leads into a more sclerotized post-atrial structure that usually appears to have one edge more sclerotized than the other. Distally, two tracheae emerge from the post-atrial structure, but these are not always apparent (e.g., 
Figs 15A–C
). The Indian species differs in having an unpaired atrium and a single, sclerotized tube emerging distally from each of its heavily sclerotized post-atrial structures (
Fig. 17
).
